  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>This is, sadly, a big-ish change.

The best way to make this change is to make an idiom that all missions use, so
that we always do this consistently.

I'll push that to "later" as a result. Patches welcome, and we might prioritize
it in the future.

I do totally agree with you, Marga, and would like to see this change.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg2331">msg2331 (view)</a></th>
   <th>Author: margamanterola</th>
   <th>Date: 2011-08-18.18:42:00</th>
   <th>
    
   </th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>I have already completed 3 missions, and in all cases I've been confused by the
fact that after completing a certain step, I'd be shown the same page again,
with a "You have completed this part of the mission" message at the bottom.

I find this very unintuitive.  What I would expect is, after correctly doing
whatever I have to do, immediately advancing to the next step.

I hope this is not much of a change.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
